posts.subject: Just throwing it out. Could be like the rest of the 2020 polls.
If there was voter fraud - you could solve this
posts.body:
with a whole lotta killin. Sorta like that "hands off" McVeigh netted for everyone.

But the problem here is that we have rascals too. Who is to say they won't be as bad or worse than these cheaters? And once you lower the bar for insurrection - everyone is gonna try it. That risk is real.

Doesn't mean this rules out the absolute need to kill certain individuals. But it does illustrate that the continuing weakness our government displays in "enforcing rules" has consequences.

After the 2000 election, systems should have been put in place to absolutely insure bad elections never happened. Yet here we are :(

Not sayin that "might makes right" isn't on the table. Just noting there is a cost to that too. Innocent citizens will fear the right even if untouched and/or protected.

If revolt does happen....the underlying cause must be removed. Feckless politicians, lying newspeople, interfering plutocrat psychopaths, all BLM and Antifa clowns.

Pandora's box though. Monsters live within the right too. How do we counter them?

So many deserve death right now. But how does one identify them and insure none escape?

We should not be here. Many truths are better off unsaid. 

I personally don't know of anyone devoted enough to do this for Donald Trump. He's just the beneficiary from our need for fair elections :(

Some might think this a good compromise. Prop him up for another 4 yrs  with real violence - then execute him at the end of his term. Not completely fair - since he didn't design an election system which could be cheated. Bloodlust is still very real. Many will pay for this election - hence the need for blood payment as compensation for losses.

Wonder if the election system could be fixed by "kill a Congressman" every week? EVERYONE gets a roll. Makes it personal.

posts.subject: Dead man switches and car bombs....
posts.body:
When you go up against a superior force - there's not much chance you'll get out alive.

Why the single greatest gift you could provide your nation are blueprints for really superior  suicide vests with dead man switches and lethal car bombs.

Yes there is a risk to you in publishing them/seeding them. Take that risk. Do it for your country.

 “And how we burned in the camps later, thinking: What would things have been like if every Security operative, when he went out at night to make an arrest, had been uncertain whether he would return alive and had to say good-bye to his family? Or if, during periods of mass arrests, as for example in Leningrad, when they arrested a quarter of the entire city, people had not simply sat there in their lairs, paling with terror at every bang of the downstairs door and at every step on the staircase, but had understood they had nothing left to lose and had boldly set up in the downstairs hall an ambush of half a dozen people with axes, hammers, pokers, or whatever else was at hand?... The Organs would very quickly have suffered a shortage of officers and transport and, notwithstanding all of Stalin's thirst, the cursed machine would have ground to a halt! If...if...We didn't love freedom enough. And even more – we had no awareness of the real situation.... We purely and simply deserved everything that happened afterward.”

― Aleksandr I. Solzhenitsyn , The Gulag Archipelago 1918–1956
